parse

protected final ReturnType parse(XPathPullParser parser)
                          throws XMLParsingException
Uses the supplied XPathPullParser to parse new instance of ReturnType. This method allows for nested parsers... i.e. a parser parses a big object, calling parsers to parse the non-primitive fields within. The parser passed in can be at the very start of the document, or at some place in the middle.

Parameters:
parser - The XPathPullParser instance to use for parsing.
Returns:
A parsed instance of ReturnType
Throws:
XMLParsingException

onNewTag

protected abstract ReturnType onNewTag(XPathPullParser pullParser,
                                       ReturnType objectToModify)
                                throws XMLParsingException
Called every time a new XML tag is encountered. In this method, it is an implementing class' responsibility to get the details it needs from the passed XPathPullParser and either modify the passed objectToModify with these details, or do nothing if the event wasn't relevant.

Parameters:
pullParser - The XPathPullParser to get details from.
objectToModify - The object to modify.
Returns:
Should be the passed in objectToModify object, with changes.
Throws:
XMLParsingException

onText

protected abstract ReturnType onText(XPathPullParser pullParser,
                                     ReturnType objectToModify)
                              throws XMLParsingException
Called every time a text or attribute field is discovered - use XPathPullParser.getCurrentValue() to get the text value itself. When this method is called, the implementing class should get the necessary information from the passed XPathPullParser, and use it to modify the passed objectToModify value before returning it.

Parameters:
pullParser - The pull parser that's encountered the text event
objectToModify - The object to modify with details from the parser.
Returns:
objectToModify
Throws:
XMLParsingException
